Few contemporary bluesmen bring fire to their party the way Johnny Winter has since his discovery in the late '60s. Since that time, Johnny's crafted his own and reinterpreted others' blues standards and rock classics including B.B. King's "Rock Me Baby," Chuck Berry's "Johnny B. Goode," and Bob Dylan's "Highway 61 Revisited" -and they're all here, as only Johnny Winter can play'em. With ferocious licks and a look like no other, Johnny Winter has stamped a unique impression on both the blues and rock 'n' roll while becoming one of contemporary music's most prolific and enduring stars. Original Recordings Produced by Johnny Winter.
